\date{2024-09-06}
\title{alternative presentation of the localic spectrum of a commutative ring}
\taxon{Construction}
\author{trebor}
\import{common}

\p{
  We can give a presentation of the [[algm-0007]] via posites. The locale #{\Spec R} is generated by symbols #{D(f)}, where #{f \in R}. We write #{D(f) \subseteq D(g)} if #{g \mid f^n} for some #{n}. We also require that, given #{D(f_i) \subseteq D(g)}, if #{g^n = \sum_i c_i f_i} for some coefficients #{c_i}, then #{\bigcup_i D(f_i) = D(g)}.
}
